                       <playit>

By chrelad
Description: Quick and light bash program
   to access your streams.
Features:
   - Keyword searching
   - Random stream selection
   - List all streams
Installation:
   If you are reading this, it's installed.
Use:
   - Display all streams
   user@host > ./playit
   - Play random stream
   user@host > ./playit rand
   - Search for and play stream
   user@host > ./playit somafm
Which players are supported:
   You can use any player to play your streams that
   supports playing streams. I use mplayer as my
   backend, as you can see from the program.
Format of file:
   One stream URL per line. The filename can
   be anything you want. You just have to change
   it in the playit program.
My playlists.txt file:

http://ice.somafm.com/lush
http://ice.somafm.com/dronezone
http://ice.somafm.com/groovesalad
http://ice.somafm.com/cliqhop
